Joan B. Plumstead, "Inferring a Sequence Generated by a
Linear Congruence", IEEE Symposium on the Foundations
of Computer Science ("FOCS"), pp. 153-159, 1982.

Jacques Stern, "Secret Linear Congruential Generators
are not Cryptographically Secure", IEEE Symposium
on the Foundations of Computer Science ("FOCS"),
pp. 421-426, 1987.

There are others, for example references [2], [3], [6]
of the Stern paper and references [2], [5] of the
Plumstead paper.
